reviews.text:
We are from LA and are passing through on a six week roadie.  Found this restaurant through a google search of reviews.  We were NOT disappointed!  Welcomed by a bevy of employees, not too loud and the decor was purely Southwest.  The chairs are hand painted and carved with beautiful scenes of the Southwest.  The food rivals our favorite restaurant in L.A.  When in Flagstaff, this place is not to be missed.  Total bill for 2 adults and 3 kids $42.00

Not too shabby!

We were staying a night in Flagstaff and decided to try this restaurant. The service wasn't unfriendly but it certainly wasn't friendly. They took forever to take our drink order. Then it was 15 minutes before they brought them to us. They took another 15 minutes after that to take our food order and its not like they were packed. 4 tables maybe. The food was terrible. Even our kids wouldn't eat their food. Next trip, this place is out!

The food is fantastic! From the huge plate of nachos to the tacos, fajitas and the strong margaritas. ..this place is a favorite of mine and my family. The portions are huge and very resonalby priced and I always take a box home with me. Try this place out!
Fast service.  Everything we  ate was wonderful. We had burritos, queso, churros, fried ice cream, enchilada, and a tamale. The salsa is very good.
The service wasn't bad, but the food was awful.

This is our main store for shopping close to home! It can be pretty spendy at times with prices, but with Just4U coupons help a lot!! They have some great deals at times. If you want quality and a variety even with Safeway brands  Safeway is great for that. They have a deli, bakery and pharmacy. They also have a Starbucks inside. The one complaint I have lately with them is their meat department. The quality of their meat isn't as great as it use to be. We've found bone grit on the pork and bones in boneless skinless chicken. Otherwise I love their produce, breads, desserts and products!! Plus you'll always get GREAT customer service and asked if you need help out!! Or you can also do self checkout instead.

All and all it's not a bad place to shop... it's a little spendy... you definitely need to watch for deals... The cashiers are pretty nice..The pharmacy and their employees are Rock Stars... Trevor is one of the pharmacist who always goes above and beyond to take care of your needs... Thank you ever so much Trevor... yes, Amy your pretty awesome... Thank you kindly... :-) :-) :-)

This store is brightly lit and well maintained. We usually go to Costco for a lot of reasons but for small and unique grocery purchases we end up at Safeway. The checkers at this location are almost always pleasant and attentive, both things that aren't always guaranteed these days.
Its a grocery store chain. The quality is good. The price is a little high, but they offer a membership discount.

The old lady in the deli is absolutely the rudest person I’ve ever met in my life she constantly makes you feel like your bothering her that you want a sandwhich rolled her eyes and got huffy puffy that I asked for bacon and proceeded to say “I guess, but that’s gonna cost more” (like I didn’t already know that) then didn’t ask me if I wanted anything else threw my snadwhich on the counter and walked away. I will never be going back there again so disappointed
Older but good store. It has home made donuts and you can get ice cream cones at the counter, sit in the store an, Enjoy them in house. One good meat market to. I love it.

OK. They haven't got everything that larger National chain stores stock. What they have is certainly sufficient AND Bashas' has what those other stores lack: cool employees, mellow vibes + fine tunes playing on their sound system. Had a great time shopping, singing along to "Paperback Writer". Shared laughter, conversation with employees + other customers. THIS makes for a great store!
The girl in the deli, I think her name is Ricki, had excellent service with me today. She had a smile and helped me get the food I needed today! I am happy to come back again.
Good place to shop. Their donuts are fresh and delicious. They have a good selection for a decent price.

I shop at Bashas' almost every day. It's convenient for me. The employees are very nice and helpful. The store is always clean. It's the best Supermarket that I know of for their Meat, Fish and Poultry. They have very reasonable prices.
